FBIS3-44730 "drchi005_t_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 Northwest Region Qinghai Secretary Addresses Plenary Session HK0601062894 Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 25 Dec 93 HK0601062894 Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] The Second Plenary Session of the Eighth Provincial CPC Committee ended in Xining yesterday afternoon after fulfilling all its tasks. The session proposed comprehensive and conscientious implementation of all the tasks set by this session so that the province will make a big stride forward in reform and construction. The session further studied the decision of the CPC Central Committee on several questions concerning the establishment of the socialist market economic structure, summed up the province's work for this year in a down-to-earth manner, and arranged next year's work according to the spirit of the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee. [passage omitted] Provincial party Secretary Yin Kesheng made a concluding speech on the relevant issues and the tasks which required proper fulfillment. He said: An important political task at present is to conscientiously study Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, volume 3 of his selected works in particular, and the decision of the CPC Central Committee on several questions concerning the establishment of the socialist market economic structure. Cadres at all levels should pay full attention to this. He continued: Cadres at various levels in all institutions should pay serious attention changing their work style and should make firm determination to bring about a significant change in their work style. [passage omitted]
